 NDS 148, 1 (2018)    DIST-FEB18                                    31 1451     
----ENDF/B-VIII.0     MATERIAL 31                                   31 1451     
-----THERMAL NEUTRON SCATTERING DATA                                31 1451     
------ENDF-6 FORMAT                                                 31 1451     
                                                                    31 1451     
 Temperatures = 296 400 500 600 700 800 1000 1200 1600 2000 K.      31 1451     
                                                                    31 1451     
 Background                                                         31 1451     
                                                                    31 1451     
 ----------                                                         31 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    31 1451     
 (LEIP) group at North Carolina State University. The thermal       31 1451     
 scattering law data for 10% porous graphite were fully developed   31 1451     
 using molecular dynamics methods [1, 2]. Vacancies were created    31 1451     
 by randomly removing atoms from the crystalline lattice. The       31 1451     
 coherent elastic cross sections were assumed to be that for a      31 1451     
 crystalline graphite structure. Ten temperatures are available in  31 1451     
 this library. The LEAPR module from NJOY code system was used to   31 1451     
 produce File 7 MT = 2, 4 data for graphite. The coherent elastic   31 1451     
 data were prepared using the cubic approximation in LEAPR/NJOY.    31 1451     
 MAT=35 and ZA=135 are used for 10% porosity reactor graphite.      31 1451     
                                                                    31 1451     
                                                                    31 1451     
